  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton|head}}\n{{Navbutton|link={{BASEPAGENAME}}|text=Shipwrecked}}\n{{Navbutton|link={{BASEPAGENAME}}/DST|text=DST}}\n{{Navbutton|end}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = Empty Bottle (DST).png\n|image = Empty Bottle Dropped (DST).png\n|stack = 20\n|spawnCode = \"messagebottleempty\"\n|droppedBy = {{Pic24|Message in a Bottle (DST)}} {{pic24|Growth Formula Starter}}\n|craft_desctiption = Not just made by hermits!\n|ingredient1 = Salt Crystals\n|multiplier1 = 1\n|ingredient2 = Ashes\n|multiplier2 = 4\n|ingredient3 = Moon Shard\n|multiplier3 = 3\n|filter = {{Pic32|Combrining Filter}}\n|tier_text = {{pic24|Combriner}} \n}}\n{{Exclusivity|Don't Starve Together}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = It's full of nothing.\n|willow = Just a boring old bottle.\n|wolfgang = Nothing inside.\n|wendy = It holds nothing but emptiness.\n|wx78 = I HAVE TAKEN AWAY YOUR PURPOSE\n|wickerbottom = This type of jar is most commonly used for canning.\n|woodie = Wish it was filled with maple syrup...\n|maxwell = It's empty inside.\n|wigfrid = This vessel might have söme use.\n|webber = It's like the jars grandma used for her preserves.\n|winona = Might as well reuse this.\n|warly = There's nothing sadder than a jam-less jam jar.\n|wortox = An empty vessel.\n|wormwood = Empty\n|wurt = There nothing in here!\n|walter = Maybe I'll use it for my bug collection, my pockets are getting full.\n|wanda = You never know when you might need an empty bottle.\n|choose = webber}}\nThe '''Empty Bottle''' is an item in ''[[Don't Starve Together]]'', introduced in ''[[Return of Them]]''. One Empty Bottle is obtained after reading a [[Message in a Bottle]].\n\nEmpty Bottles are used to trade with the [[Crabby Hermit]]. They can also be used to craft [[Growth Formula Starter|Growth Formula]], which returns one empty bottle when used. When an [[Icker]] drops globs, Empty Bottles can be used to create [[Icker Jar|Icker Jars]].\n\n== {{Pic32|Icon Tools}} Usage ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Kelp Fronds\n|item3 = Ash\n|tool = Science Machine\n|result = Growth Formula Starter\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Marble\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Red Gem\n|result =Soul Jar\n|character = Wortox\n|skill = Soul Jar (Skill)\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Petals\n|count2 = 8 / 6 / 4\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Petal Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Dark Petals\n|count2 = 8 / 6 / 4\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Dark Petal Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Foliage\n|count2 = 8 / 6 / 4\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Foliage Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Succulent\n|count2 = 6 / 4 / 2\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Succulent Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Lune Tree Blossom\n|count2 = 8 / 6 / 4\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Lune Tree Blossom Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Fire Nettle Frond\n|count2 = 6 / 4 / 2\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Fire Nettle Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Tillweed\n|count2 = 6 / 4 / 2\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Tillweed Tea\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Empty Bottle (DST)\n|item2 = Dried Forget-Me-Lots\n|count2 = 6 / 4 / 2\n|tool = Pearl's Tea Shop\n|result = Forget-Me-Lots Tea\n}}\n== {{Pic|32|Placeholder}}Trivia ==\n* Empty Bottles were introduced to ''Don't Starve Together'' in the ''[[Return of Them#She Sells Sea Shells|She Sells Sea Shells]]'' update.\n* The fact that the glass color of the bottle has a slightly turquoise tint may indicate that it is made from moon glass ([[Moon Shard]]). This may explain how Pearl makes these bottles.\n\n\n{{Resources}}\n[[es:Botella vacía]]\n[[pl:Pustka Butelka (DSS)]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[Category:Ocean]]\n[[Category:Items]]\n[[Category:Naturally Spawning Objects]]\n[[Category:Resources]]\n[[Category:Refine Tab]]\n[[Category:Return of Them]]"
